Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 10 October 2023
Crypto Banter values and respects your privacy. This Privacy and Cookie Policy (“Privacy Policy”) explains how you may use and access Crypto Banter.com (the “Website” or “Site”), and associated content, software, and mobile applications (collectively, the “Service” or “Services”).
This Privacy Policy explains when and why we collect personal information about people who visit our Website or use our Services, and how and when we use this and keep it secure. We also explain how we use cookies and similar technology on our Website for our Services.
We may change this Privacy Policy from time to time, so please check this page occasionally to ensure that you are happy with any changes.
By using our Website or our Services, you are agreeing to be bound by this Privacy Policy. Do not use any of our Services if you do not agree with our Privacy Policy.
This Privacy Policy does not apply to any information collected via third-party websites accessed through our Services, or to any information submitted by you to us through email, text messages or other electronic communication.
European Union (EU) residents are requested to review our EU Data section below to see our legal bases for processing and transfer of your data.
What information do we collect?
Crypto Banter gathers information about our readers in the following ways:
Information you provide
We may collect your contact information (e.g. email address, phone number etc.), or other information you provide in feedback, marketing activities, complaints, customer support, and other forms of correspondence.
We may also collect other data, such as how you use our service and connect with us, technical data such as your crypto wallet addresses (e.g. for KYC or airdrop purposes), and marketing communication preferences such as newsletters.
Information from other parties
We may add to the information you provide more information from other third party sources.
Automatically collected information
Crypto Banter may automatically collect the following analytical information, in order to improve and optimize our Service by better understanding the user experience and needs:
certain website usage information (“Site Log Data”), for example user IP addresses, device, operating system and browser;
site pages and features visited;
duration and frequency of visits;
web search terms or keywords used to navigate to site.
How do we use your information?
Delivery of service
In order to give you the best possible Crypto Banter experience, we use your personal info to give you access to our Services and the ability to use them, to enable and deliver requested products and services to you, and to send important information, such as technical updates, notices, security warnings, email confirmations, support and general administrative communication.
Legal compliance
We use your personal information as we believe necessary or appropriate to comply with applicable laws, lawful requests and legal process, such as to respond to subpoenas or requests from government authorities.
We may use your personal information at our discretion as necessary in order to meet applicable laws and legal requests and processes by authorities, such as subpoenas.
Communication with you
We may selectively use your personal info to inform you about promotions, events, products, and services from our selected partners.
Website enhancement
We may use your personal info to improve your site experience and our Services, such as optimizing our layout, answering questions, enhancing our customer support, and protecting our users against illicit or fraudulent behavior and activity.
If you give consent, we may share your testimonials or endorsements, or give you the choice to opt into third party marketing activities.
How do we share your personal information?
Crypto Banter will under no circumstances share with or sell your personal information to third parties without your express consent, except as explained in this Privacy Policy.
We may disclose personal information to third parties in the following conditions:
Subsidiaries and Affiliates for purposes consistent with this Privacy Policy;
Business-related transfers or deals, such as a merger, financing, acquisition, or bankruptcy transaction or proceeding;
Compliance for legal, protection, safety and emergency purposes. This includes compliance with laws and authorities, and protecting our business, customers, employees, and other people;
Professional advisors and service providers who we may use to conduct work for us, such as third parties that help us provide the Service (e.g. customer support, website hosting, database, legal and financial service providers);
Other companies or entities you permit us to share your information with, as well as aggregated and anonymous data, which will be subject to the third party entities’ privacy policies.
How do we secure your personal information?
Crypto Banter will only keep your information as long as we feel it’s necessary and needed for the purposes described in this document.
We’ll also keep personal information at our discretion (in consideration of your rights and sensitivity of the data) to comply with laws where needed, help with legal investigations, fix disputes and problems, and deter fraudulent actions.
Where required, we may anonymize your data, ensuring that your information is not identifiable in any way, and use it indefinitely without giving you any further notice.
We use industry-approved security measures and technology to protect your personal information as it is submitted through our Services; however, we cannot guarantee its security due to the nature of online traffic.
We will not be held responsible for the interception or interruption of internet-relayed communication and losses of data.
Our Service users are responsible for ensuring and maintaining their password and biometric security, user ID and other sensitive information that could be harmfully used against them.
We may suspend your use of our Services without informing you, for your own protection and/or the protection of our other users, if we suspect a security breach or issue.
Cross-border transfers
The Company is not located in the EU nor the United States, but we may have affiliates and service providers in these jurisdictions or other countries around the world. This means your personal information may be shared as detailed in this document with entities in other countries or jurisdictions with different privacy laws from those in your jurisdiction.
We advise our European Union (EU) users to read the information below regarding the transfer of personal information outside of the European Economic Area (EEA).
Children and our services
If you are under age in your jurisdiction, you may only use the Services with the approval and/or supervision of your parent or legal guardian. In alignment with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA), if we discover we’ve received information from a child younger than age 13 without parental consent, we will use this information only to reply to the child or their parent to inform them they are not permitted to use our our Site, after which we will permanently delete it.
By using the Crypto Banter service, you represent that you are at least 18 years old, or that you are at least 13 years old and have your parents’ or guardians’ permission to use the Service.
California privacy rights
In accordance with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), we inform you that in the last year, Crypto Banter may have collected, utilized and shared for business reasons personal information about you as per this Privacy Policy. Residents of California have the right to request access to and the deleting of this information we hold about them by emailing info@cryptobanter.com
Crypto Banter will not sell your personal information without your consent, nor discriminate against you for exercising your rights under CCPA. specifically such as:
Denying you access to our Services;
Charging a higher rate for the use of our Services; or
Providing you with a decreased quality of service.
GDPR compliance for EU residents
Residents in the European Union should consider the following: “Personal information,” as used in this Privacy Policy, is the same as “personal data” as defined in the
European Union General Data Protection Regulation
(GDPR).
You may be providing us with sensitive data as defined in the GDPR’s special categories of personal data, such as your racial or ethnic identification as per your government-issued identification documents.
We’ll use your personal information in accordance with the law, and will inform you as required of the legal bases of the processing of your personal information. Please contact info@cryptobanter.com if you require more information.
