Your rights
The GDPR gives you specific rights pertaining to your personal information. You are entitled to ask us to take the following actions regarding your personal information we hold:
Opt-out: To cease the sending of direct marketing communications which you have previously agreed to receive. We may, however, continue to send you communication related to our Service or for non-marketing reasons;
Access: To explain how we process your personal information and give you access to it;
Update: To update or correct inaccuracies in your personal information;
Delete: To delete your personal information;
Transfer: To transfer a machine-readable copy of your personal information to you or a third party of your choice;
Restrict: To restrict the processing of your personal information;
Object. To object to any processing of your personal information that impacts your rights.
You can submit these requests by email to info@cryptobanter.com.
We may ask for specific information to help us verify your identity and fulfil your request, in accordance with applicable law. If we decline your request, we’ll inform you if we are legally allowed. To lodge a complaint, please contact us at info@cryptobanter.com or complain to your domestic data protection authority, which you may find
here
.
Our Cookies Policy
Last Updated: 22 December 2021
Crypto Banter may utilize cookies or related technology (such as Google Analytics and Google Search Console) to analyze trends, improve website administration, user navigational tracking and demographic breakdown. You can control the usage of cookies by changing the settings on your browser.
Learn more about how Google Analytics uses your personal data here:
https://www.google.com/analytics/terms/us.html
Warning: We will NEVER ask you to share your private key or wallet seed with us. If you are asked this information, you are likely being targeted by a phishing scam looking to steal your funds.
Why do we need to use cookies?
We respect your privacy, and therefore we would like to clearly explain how we use cookies on the Site.
A cookie is a small text file, which often includes an anonymous unique identifier, which is placed on your harddrive by a web page server. Cookies are required to use some Crypto Banter services.
Crypto Banter and its ad management partners use cookies to capture current session information, and may also occasionally use web beacons (such as internet tags, pixel tags, and clear GIFs).
Without some cookies, we wouldn’t be able to deliver the many Services we do on our site. We use cookies to better understand our users. For example, cookies allow us to recognize new or past users and Site behavior, to save your registered password for faster logins, to optimize our Site and gain insights into how you use it and how people browse across other websites and platforms.
We and our marketing partners, service providers and affiliates use cookies, web beacons, pixels, and other technologies to ensure an optimal experience for all our users.
We may also use third-party cookies for marketing reasons.
Cookies might be “session” cookies (which we delete after your session), or “persistent” cookies (which will remain until you or the cookie server delete them).
You can disable cookies by following the recommendations of your browser.
You can opt out of Google Analytics data collection with the
Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on
and learn additional information about managing cookies at
http://www.allaboutcookies.org/manage-cookies/
.
